text:
*COMO ADMINISTRADOR DEL SLACK*
    He detectado, la preferencia de algunos usuarios de mantener este slack, organizado, según la temática del contenido de los mensajes o incluso siguiendo otros criterios.
    He de decir, que lamentablemente, no se han seguido los criterios que al principio se intentaron hacer cumplir: libertad de crear los canales para cada temática que se propusieran y crear canales para que cada usuario se sienta cómodo en su idioma que prefiera utilizar habitualmente, y dejar el canal "MODHARBOUR" únicamente para comentarios sobre mod-harbour.
    Hay canales para todos los gustos, y si no los hay, es muy sencillo crearlos, bien por parte de los usuarios o en cualquier caso, yo los puedo crear: cualquier temática o criterio organizativo, serán bienvenidos. Por ejemplo, hay un canal MVC que lleva mucho mucho tiempo abierto y que nadie utiliza, otro para GENESIS, etc.
    Para no tener que volver a hablar sobre este tema, y evitar discrepancias entre los usuarios, os agradezco que todos cumplamos estas normas y conseguiremos además que el slack quede perfectamente organizado.

text:
*AS ADMINISTRATOR OF THE SLACK*
    I have detected the preference of some users to keep this slack organized, according to the subject of the content of the messages or even following other criteria.
    I have to say that, unfortunately, the criteria that we tried to enforce at the beginning have not been followed: freedom to create channels for each topic proposed and also create channels so that each user feels comfortable in their language that they prefer to use regularly. , and leave the channel "MODHARBOUR" only for comments on mod-harbor.
    There are channels for all tastes, and if there are not, it is very easy to create them, either by the users or in any case, I can create them: any theme or organizational criteria will be welcome. For example, there is an MVC channel that has been open for a long, long time and that nobody uses, another for GENESIS, etc.
    To avoid having to talk about this again, and to avoid discrepancies between users, I thank you all for complying with these rules and we will also ensure that slack is perfectly organized.

    There are channels for all tastes, and if there are not, it is very easy to create them, either by the users or in any case, I can create them: any theme or organizational criteria will be welcome. For example, there is an MVC channel that has been open for a long, long time and that nobody uses, another for GENESIS, etc.
    To avoid having to talk about this again, and to avoid discrepancies between users, I thank you all for complying with these rules and we will also ensure that slack is perfectly organized.
